modules.description: This module provides direct conversions between low-level system handles and their numeric representations, specifically working with `Unix.dir_handle` and `Unix.file_descr` types. It exposes functions to convert directory handles to `nativeint` and back, as well as file descriptors to `int` and vice versa. These operations are useful when interfacing with C libraries or system calls that expect raw numeric identifiers for file and directory handles.
